      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">37.105</ph> Competition in service contracting.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d2357e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d2382e10">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
						            Unless otherwise provided by statute, contracts for services shall be awarded through sealed bidding whenever the conditions in <xref href="6.401.dita#FAR_6_401"
                        base="i1119378"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">6.401</xref>(a) are met, (except see <xref href="6.401.dita#FAR_6_401"
                        base="i1119378"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">6.401</xref>(b)).</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d2382e21">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
						            The provisions of statute and <xref href="Part_6.dita#FAR_Part_6"
                        base="i1120119"
                        outputclass="fm:Part"
                        class="- topic/xref ">partÂ  6</xref> of this regulation requiring competition apply fully to service contracts. The method of contracting used to provide for competition may vary with the type of service being acquired and may not necessarily be limited to price competition.</p>
            </li>
